duck.heading: Oil
duck.definition: oil definition: any of numerous unctuous combustible substances that are liquid or can be liquefied easily on warming, are soluble in ether but not in water, and leave a greasy stain on paper or cloth.

wiki.text:
An 'oil' is any neutral, nonpolar chemical substance, that is a viscous liquid
at ambient temperatures, and is immiscible with water but soluble in alcohols or
ethers. Oils have a high carbon and hydrogen content and are usually flammable
and slippery. Oils may be animal, vegetable, or petrochemical in origin, and may
be volatile or non-volatile.<ref></ref>
wiki.title: Oil
